The paper deals with the decidability of a theory and provides a syntactic algorithm for quantifier elimination, which suggests that it belongs to the logic (cs.LO) and computational complexity (cs.CC) categories. The use of iterated exponentiation and the focus on the complexity of the decision procedure suggest connections to the discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and scientific computing (cs.SC) categories. Finally, the application of the theory to real-world problems and the use of model theory suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
